Privacy Policy for BacHelper

BacHelper ("the App") is developed as an educational application designed to help students prepare for their exams through lessons, study sessions, and interactive videos.

1. Information We Collect

BacHelper does not collect, store, or share any personal data from users.
The only data saved on your device are local preferences such as:

Study sessions

Completed lessons

Subject progress
These are stored locally using SharedPreferences and are not shared with anyone.

2. Permissions Used

The app may request the following permissions:

Notification permission: to remind you of study sessions.

Internet access: to play YouTube educational videos.
No background tracking or sensitive data collection occurs.

3. Third-Party Services

The app uses:

YouTube API to display educational videos.
YouTube may collect some data as described in their Privacy Policy
.

4. Data Security

All your progress and data remain stored locally on your device.
We do not collect analytics or transmit your information to any external servers.

5. Changes to This Policy

This policy may be updated from time to time. Updates will be available within the app or on the app store listing.

6. Contact Us

